
            Video
            Did Commons Leader Andrea Leadsom just 'flounce'?
            Commons leader Andrea Leadsom showed off her flouncing skills to MPs earlier after a Labour MP apologised to her for using the word.Barry Sheerman said he should not have said Mrs Leadsom "flounced" out of an earlier debate because it was a "sexist" term.Mrs Leadsom said no apology was necessary - and showed MPs how it's done.(According to the Oxford English Dictionary, flounce means to "go or move in an exaggeratedly impatient or angry manner").
                
                        06 Dec 2018
                    
                
        
